                     <td width="100%" class="TableCellAlternate">
                        <h1><a name="6997"></a><a href="/blogs/readMore.html?id=6997">Shards trundles along</a></h1>
                        <div class="ItemInfo">[<a href="/blogs/selectBlog.html?id=2729&amp;articleId=6997" alt="Use this to refer to the specific blog entry">URL</a>] Posted on 7 June 2004 20:20,  <a href="/blogs/readMore.html?id=6997">0 comments in 0 threads.</a> Last comment on 7 June 2004 20:20.
                        </div>
                        <div>I have been working on the Shards project for the last few days. The first attempt I put up required some interesting changes
                           - I use the Willow font as the main headlining font and Papyrus to announce its name and Georgia for the body text. It didn't
                           work out so well, so now eveything is Papyrus (headline + title) and Palintino Linotype (James' suggestion) and it looks pretty
                           good. 
                           <p></p>
                           
                           I also changed the background from the attack on a lonely road to the party looking out across a valley from a lonely ruin.
                           I don't have the second image in very high resolution and it clearly isn't finally done (its in pencil, Paul who works for
                           Weta as his day job and is pretty busy has yet to ink it). 
                           <p></p>
                           
                           But I have found it may take a while to get the layout quite right. One other thing we are doing is simple caricatures of
                           important NPCs for all of our material. The images aren't fantastic quality, but they do convey the essence of an NPC, at
                           least, I hope :-)
                           <p></p>
                           
                           Thats all for this long Queens Birthday weekend, I am just waiting on some confirmation from James that I got a migration
                           from 3rd circle Elf Troubadour to 4th circle Human troubadour right before I update the PDF again for those on the Shards
                           project. Then I need the final art from Paul, and then when it is accepted by James, it goes into the hands of FASA and then
                           onto the web site for final delivery. Hopefully that will be sooner than a few weeks away!
                           <p></p>
                        </div><br></td>
                  </tr>
