                        <h1><a name="2754"></a><a href="/blogs/readMore.html?id=2754">testing out a new deployment mechanism</a></h1>
                        <div class="ItemInfo">[<a href="/blogs/selectBlog.html?id=2729&amp;articleId=2754" alt="Use this to refer to the specific blog entry">URL</a>] Posted on 4 June 2004 10:00,  <a href="/blogs/readMore.html?id=2754">0 comments in 0 threads.</a> Last comment on 4 June 2004 10:00.
                        </div>
                        <div>Sorry for the up and down on the web site - it'll probably go on for another hour or so while i figure out the kinks. The
                           intention is to make the process of deploying new functionality less time consuming and less likely to take the web site down
                           for too long. I have created a staging area that will hold all the updates and then deployment is simply a web server down
                           / copy / web server up. But making sure I have all the right bits deployed...
                           
                           Thats what I'm working on now!
                        </div><br></td>
